des:
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust the power state of your plug- just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
After connecting Alexa to your "EdiSmart Pro" products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "EdiSmart Pro" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3). Turn on EdiSmart Pro devices and connect them with “EdiSmart Pro” app;
(4). IMPORTANT: You can rename the devices with "EdiSmart Pro" App. So if you rename a smart plug “Livingroom plug”, then Echo will get that same name after discovered the devices in Step 9;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market, and connect Echo with "Alexa" app;
(6). Search the Alexa Skills directory for "EdiSmart Pro";
(7). Click Enable skill of "EdiSmart Pro", then input your account username, password and region on the linking page;
(8). Talk to Echo "Alexa,discover devices.”. Wait till Echo says "Discover is completed";
(9). Now all setup is done. Try talk to Echo to control your devices.
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on the smart plug"
“Alexa, turn off the smart plug"
